  "response": "A cake mix is a pre-packaged dry ingredient blend used to make cakes quickly and easily. It typically contains flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and sometimes powdered milk or other additives. To make a cake, you usually just need to add wet ingredients like eggs, oil, and water to the mix, stir, and then bake. Cake mixes come in various flavors like chocolate, vanilla, and yellow cake, and are designed to simplify the cake-baking process for home cooks.",
